I've made a point to visit Natural Blend every time I've been in the neighborhood for the past two years. This is a great place for lunch or a quick snack, but most people seem to take their order to go due to the small size of the place and the limited seating. What Natural Blend lacks in size it more than makes up with flavors on its comprehensive daily menu of vegan Caribbean delights, from hearty baked goods to delectable fresh juices to (my all-time favorite) barbecue spare ribs made with soy protein. I don't know who owns it, but this place gives one the impression of a real "Mom and Pop" shop. The staff is knowledgeable and quick to serve the line of guests that usually stretches out onto the sidewalk, but they don't seem to say anything on the rare occasion when a patron particularly eager for plant-based food skips the queued customers. In spite of all this, Natural Blend is the kind of place that I will always go to taste something that is all at once delicious, comforting, and healthy.
